Project Pharos

Description:
  A small APRS beacon for the tracking of the golden lion tamarin monkey was prototyped. The beacon was required to be low power and use GPS as a source of position acquisition.

Main Components:
  MSP430G2553
  RadioMetrix HX1 @ 144.390 MHz
  GP-2103 SiRF IV GPS
  CR2450 Battery

Schematic, Eagle files, and parts list can be found in Hardware Folder.

How to use:
  1) Construct the board as described.
  2) Install Code Composer Studio  V5.3.0 or greater
  3) Connect TEST RST GND pins from MSP430 Launchpad to TEST RST GND pins on final board.
  4) ???
  5) Profit

  